706763f-b.text:
Shore Parkway, east from about Plumb 1st Street, showing this Brooklyn section of the Belt Parkway, formerly known as the Circumferential Parkway, under construction. Much of this parkway was built on hydraulic fill taken from
Sheepshead Bay.
View 1: July 9, 1936
Views 2,3: June 13, 1940
P. L. Sperr
